<BYLINE>
   By WILLIAM DAWKINS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE French government said yesterday it did not plan to suspend Japanese car
imports, writes William Dawkins from Paris.
Mr Dominique Strauss-Kahn, industry and trade minister, said France believed
in the EC-Japan car import accord signed in July 1991, which had been 'more
than respected' by Japanese car exporters to France.
