FT  06 JAN 93 / Unions plan jobs campaign
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UNIONS representing 5.8m public-sector workers agreed last night to
co-ordinate a campaign against government policies which they say are
threatening jobs and services.
After a meeting at Trades Union Congress headquarters in London, union
leaders said their members felt 'deep anger' about the damage caused by
government policies.
