 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
WRECKS THAT MADE THE HEADLINES
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Between January and June 1942 German U-Boats torpedoed a number of
tankers off the east coast of the US with a loss of some 600,000 tonnes
of oil. The grounding of the Exxon Valdez in Prince William Sound,
Alaska, on 24 March 1989 ranks outside the 10 worst spills at about
35,000 tonnes, but resulted in major ecological damage.
In addition to these major slicks, it is estimated that an average of
2,000,000 tonnes is spilled into the world's seas every year. The
tanker, Aegean Sea, ran aground of La Coruna in northwest Spain in early
December, spilling 500,000 barrels of oil.
