<HEADLINE>
FT  06 JAN 93 / US to step up efforts to collect heavy weapons in Somalia
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The US is about to step up efforts to collect heavy weapons from armed
factions in Somalia, special envoy Robert Oakley said yesterday, Reuter
reports from Washington.
Mr Oakley said the move was possible 'now that we have more forces on the
ground and those forces have more mobility - helicopters for example, some
of which are just arriving this week'.
The extent to which US troops try to disarm the warring factions has been
the subject of debate between the Bush administration and the United
Nations. Mr Boutros Boutros Ghali, UN secretary-general, has pressed
Washington to take a more activist role.
