FT  06 JAN 93 / Problems for Russia's new private farmers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Shortage of cash and soaring prices are causing problems for Russia's new
private farmers, Itar-Tass news agency said yesterday, Reuter reports from
Moscow.
Tass quoted Mr Vladimir Bashmachnikov, president of the Association of
Russian Farmers, as saying that the government's failure to finalise laws on
