<HEADLINE>
FT  06 JAN 93 / Sterling enjoys remarkable rally against D-Mark
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sterling enjoyed a remarkable rally against the D-Mark yesterday, rising by
more than 5 pfennigs as investor concern grew over the French franc. The
pound closed at DM2.51, up 5 1/4 pfennigs, a level it maintained in New
York. It was also strong against the dollar, finishing more than 4 cents
higher in London at Dollars 1.5455 and rising to Dollars 1.550 in New York.
There were suggestions that speculation against weaker currencies in the
ERM, including the French franc, had given the pound a temporary status as a
'safe haven'.
London shares, however, finished sharply lower. The FT-SE 100 index closed
27.9 points down at 2,833.6.
